00:37:00.756 --> 00:37:03.946 A:middle
And that's how easy that is.

00:37:04.546 --> 00:37:04.886 A:middle
Thank you.

00:37:05.386 --> 00:37:07.836 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:37:08.336 --> 00:37:10.616 A:middle
&gt;&gt; All right, let's talk about
a few additional controls,

00:37:11.086 --> 00:37:13.796 A:middle
the pause button and the
player indicator LED's.

00:37:14.886 --> 00:37:18.086 A:middle
Now, the hardware
spec guarantees

00:37:18.086 --> 00:37:20.146 A:middle
that every controller
has a pause button.

00:37:20.436 --> 00:37:25.596 A:middle
And if your game supports game
controllers you must support

00:37:26.366 --> 00:37:30.366 A:middle
or you must handle the
pause button being pressed.

00:37:30.366 --> 00:37:32.446 A:middle
And you're going to want
to treat this as a toggle.

00:37:32.506 --> 00:37:35.526 A:middle
Go from pause to unpause
and unpause back to paused.

00:37:36.766 --> 00:37:39.166 A:middle
Consider your UI
state, some situations

00:37:39.166 --> 00:37:41.436 A:middle
in your game it maybe
appropriate to do nothing.

00:37:41.436 --> 00:37:45.156 A:middle
Let's look at an example.

00:37:45.156 --> 00:37:47.516 A:middle
So, were back inside of our
setup controllers method

00:37:48.396 --> 00:37:49.856 A:middle
and its really as
simple as this,

00:37:50.476 --> 00:37:52.696 A:middle
whenever you have a controller
that your game is going to use,

00:37:53.516 --> 00:37:55.466 A:middle
use the controller
paused handler,

00:37:56.416 --> 00:37:59.836 A:middle
set that up in this case
whenever the controllers pause

00:37:59.836 --> 00:38:00.666 A:middle
button is pressed.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:38:00.936 --> 00:38:06.966 A:middle
This block is run and we toggle
the pause state of the game.

00:38:07.146 --> 00:38:08.296 A:middle
Also controllers are going

00:38:08.296 --> 00:38:10.516 A:middle
to have player indicator
LED's on them.

00:38:11.726 --> 00:38:13.316 A:middle
And it's your job
to assign these.

00:38:14.146 --> 00:38:15.506 A:middle
These communicates
to your player

00:38:15.506 --> 00:38:18.506 A:middle
that your game has recognized
the controller and is using it.

00:38:18.556 --> 00:38:21.826 A:middle
And in the case of multi
controller games we will give

00:38:21.826 --> 00:38:23.116 A:middle
the player an indication as to

00:38:23.116 --> 00:38:24.846 A:middle
which player they
are in your game.

00:38:26.676 --> 00:38:31.226 A:middle
These LED's are persistent and
so as a controller disconnects

00:38:31.226 --> 00:38:34.896 A:middle
and reconnects its going to
maintain the same player index.

00:38:35.436 --> 00:38:41.176 A:middle
Now, the player index property
on a controller is what you use

00:38:41.176 --> 00:38:42.786 A:middle
to set the player
indicator LED's.

00:38:42.786 --> 00:38:47.296 A:middle
We have a constant called
GCControllerPlayerIndexUnset.

00:38:47.296 --> 00:38:50.016 A:middle
And in this example
were checking

00:38:50.016 --> 00:38:52.326 A:middle
if the indexes indeed
unset and if

00:38:52.326 --> 00:38:54.136 A:middle
so assigning it to player one.

00:38:55.306 --> 00:38:57.316 A:middle
You'll notice we have a
zero based index game.

00:38:57.876 --> 00:39:02.346 A:middle
In a multiple controller
game you might check if any

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:39:02.346 --> 00:39:05.146 A:middle
of the currently connected
controllers are unset and if

00:39:05.216 --> 00:39:08.536 A:middle
so display a UI to the player
so that they can choose

00:39:08.796 --> 00:39:10.786 A:middle
which players go on
which teams for instance.

00:39:13.296 --> 00:39:13.846 A:middle
All right.

00:39:13.846 --> 00:39:16.736 A:middle
Now, that you have all the
technical information let's take

00:39:16.736 --> 00:39:20.586 A:middle
a step back and talk about best
practices following these you're

00:39:20.586 --> 00:39:22.886 A:middle
going to be able to integrate
game controllers in a way

00:39:22.886 --> 00:39:24.686 A:middle
that really makes
sense and works

00:39:24.686 --> 00:39:25.766 A:middle
with the player's intentions.

00:39:26.276 --> 00:39:28.666 A:middle
So, first of all just

00:39:28.666 --> 00:39:31.416 A:middle
to reiterate games cannot
require a controller.

00:39:32.766 --> 00:39:34.806 A:middle
Game controllers are
optional for players.

00:39:35.456 --> 00:39:38.356 A:middle
You're going to want
to focus your efforts

00:39:38.356 --> 00:39:41.016 A:middle
on the native controls
of the system.

00:39:41.306 --> 00:39:43.636 A:middle
So, that means touch
and motion on iOS

00:39:43.636 --> 00:39:45.786 A:middle
and keyboard and mouse on OS X.

00:39:45.786 --> 00:39:49.026 A:middle
And this is so that you
can reach a hundred percent

00:39:49.026 --> 00:39:50.456 A:middle
of the players who
play your game.

00:39:51.676 --> 00:39:55.206 A:middle
For the players who buy a
gamepad controller you can offer

00:39:55.206 --> 00:39:58.066 A:middle
them the enhanced experience
that you're going to create.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:40:00.916 --> 00:40:03.526 A:middle
Also, follow standard
gameplay conventions.

00:40:03.926 --> 00:40:08.136 A:middle
So, the face buttons A and B you
can use those and we recommend

00:40:08.136 --> 00:40:10.826 A:middle
that you use them as the
A button being your action

00:40:10.826 --> 00:40:14.416 A:middle
or confirmation button and the B
button being your cancel button.

00:40:15.066 --> 00:40:17.906 A:middle
Now, when talking
about connecting

00:40:17.906 --> 00:40:21.686 A:middle
and disconnecting think of this
from the player's perspective.

00:40:22.056 --> 00:40:24.286 A:middle
There's player intent
behind each

00:40:24.286 --> 00:40:26.056 A:middle
of these notifications
that you get.

00:40:26.956 --> 00:40:29.956 A:middle
When you have a connected
event the player has plugged

00:40:29.956 --> 00:40:33.646 A:middle
in their controller into the
game, or into your device

00:40:34.266 --> 00:40:35.916 A:middle
and they want to play
with the controller.

00:40:36.536 --> 00:40:40.686 A:middle
And so, in that case off
load some of the native input

00:40:41.206 --> 00:40:43.636 A:middle
on to the controller
wherever appropriate.

00:40:45.146 --> 00:40:47.636 A:middle
Also eliminate the
player indicator LED's

00:40:48.026 --> 00:40:49.206 A:middle
so that the player knows

00:40:49.206 --> 00:40:51.136 A:middle
that the game has
recognized the controllers

00:40:51.136 --> 00:40:52.226 A:middle
and is ready to use them.

00:40:52.806 --> 00:40:56.446 A:middle
And lastly, a lot of games have

00:40:56.446 --> 00:40:58.866 A:middle
on screen overlays
like a pause button.

00:40:59.166 --> 00:41:01.426 A:middle
This is entirely appropriate
for a touch base game.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:41:01.426 --> 00:41:04.796 A:middle
But with a controller connected
the controller already has a

00:41:04.796 --> 00:41:08.596 A:middle
pause button so you can
offload that on screen element

00:41:08.676 --> 00:41:10.556 A:middle
to the controller freeing

00:41:10.556 --> 00:41:12.716 A:middle
up additional real
estate on your screen.

00:41:13.916 --> 00:41:16.646 A:middle
Similarly when disconnecting the
player is saying I don't want

00:41:16.646 --> 00:41:18.526 A:middle
to use this controller
any longer at the moment

00:41:19.126 --> 00:41:21.546 A:middle
or maybe there is elements
or maybe there's reasons

00:41:21.546 --> 00:41:23.946 A:middle
out of their control why this
controller happen to disconnect.

00:41:24.726 --> 00:41:27.196 A:middle
In either case, pause
the gameplay

00:41:27.196 --> 00:41:28.416 A:middle
if you're engaged in gameplay.

00:41:29.156 --> 00:41:33.666 A:middle
Also, return to regular controls
'cause the game has no guarantee

00:41:33.666 --> 00:41:35.516 A:middle
that the player is
going to return back

00:41:35.666 --> 00:41:37.266 A:middle
with controller based controls.

00:41:41.336 --> 00:41:43.876 A:middle
And lastly, think
through your input

00:41:44.606 --> 00:41:49.666 A:middle
so as Jacques mentioned touch
controls allow you amazing

00:41:49.666 --> 00:41:52.866 A:middle
abilities to directly manipulate
your onscreen objects.

00:41:53.696 --> 00:41:56.156 A:middle
And controllers are
great for other tasks

00:41:56.516 --> 00:42:01.316 A:middle
like precise inputs filling the
tactile feedback of the buttons

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:42:01.316 --> 00:42:03.056 A:middle
in the controllers
against your fingers.

00:42:03.946 --> 00:42:05.716 A:middle
Repeatability of actions.

00:42:06.236 --> 00:42:10.756 A:middle
And there's real magic we think
in marrying these two together.

00:42:11.256 --> 00:42:13.646 A:middle
And as game designers
you have to think

00:42:13.646 --> 00:42:17.586 A:middle
about what game mechanics make
most sense with touch and motion

00:42:17.746 --> 00:42:20.306 A:middle
and which ones makes
most sense to use

00:42:20.306 --> 00:42:21.786 A:middle
as physical controller inputs.

